THOUGHT: The remaining miscompile is because we build a shift-amount vector by shuffling the compare vector and leaving other lanes undef. For vector shifts of i1, any lane with a non-zero or poison/undef shift amount is undefined and can propagate poison across lanes in Alive2’s modeling. To avoid UB on irrelevant lanes, we must ensure those lanes have a zero shift amount. I will change createShiftShuffle to use a two-source shuffle with the second source being a zero vector, and a mask that selects the desired element from the first source only for the NewIndex lane, while all other lanes take zero from the second source.

```bash
applypatch << 'EOF'
*** Begin Patch
*** Update File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp
@@
 static Value *createShiftShuffle(Value *Vec, unsigned OldIndex,
                                  unsigned NewIndex, IRBuilder<> &Builder) {
-  // The shuffle mask is poison except for 1 lane that is being translated
-  // to the new element index. Example for OldIndex == 2 and NewIndex == 0:
-  // ShufMask = { 2, poison, poison, poison }
-  auto *VecTy = cast<FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType());
-  SmallVector<int, 32> ShufMask(VecTy->getNumElements(), PoisonMaskElem);
-  ShufMask[NewIndex] = OldIndex;
-  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, ShufMask, "shift");
+  // Build a shuffle that places the element OldIndex from the first source
+  // into lane NewIndex. All other lanes must be well-defined zero to avoid
+  // undefined behavior in subsequent vector shifts of i1.
+  auto *VecTy = cast<FixedVectorType>(Vec->getType());
+  unsigned VF = VecTy->getNumElements();
+  // Create a zero vector for the second source.
+  Value *ZeroVec = Constant::getNullValue(VecTy);
+  // Mask selects OldIndex from first source at NewIndex and zeros from second
+  // source for all other lanes.
+  SmallVector<int, 32> ShufMask(VF);
+  for (unsigned I = 0; I != VF; ++I)
+    ShufMask[I] = VF + I; // select lane I from ZeroVec
+  ShufMask[NewIndex] = OldIndex; // select from first source for the target lane
+  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, ZeroVec, ShufMask);
 }
*** End Patch
EOF
&& submit-patch
```

