THOUGHT: The miscompile is triggered when VectorCombine folds scalar compares into a vector compare even though the compare feeds an i1 shift. Vectorizing creates undefined lanes that poison the result. A safe fix is to avoid folding extracted compares when the compare feeds a shift of i1. I will modify foldExtractExtract to early-return false in that case, preventing the unsafe transform.

```bash
python3 - << 'PY'
import re
p = "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VectorCombine.cpp"
s = open(p).read()
# Insert a guard before calling foldExtExtCmp/foldExtExtBinop:
insert_point = re.search(r'\n\s*if \(Pred != CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE\)\s*', s)
if insert_point:
    guard = """
  // Avoid folding extracted compares if they feed an i1 shift, as vectorizing
  // the compare can introduce undefined lanes that poison the result.
  if (Pred != CmpInst::BAD_ICMP_PREDICATE) {
    for (llvm::User *U : I.users()) {
      if (auto *BO = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::BinaryOperator>(U)) {
        if ((BO->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::AShr ||
             BO->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::LShr ||
             BO->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::Shl) &&
            I.getType()->isIntegerTy(1))
          return false;
      }
    }
  }
"""
    s = s[:insert_point.start()] + guard + s[insert_point.start():]
    open(p, "w").write(s)
    print("Inserted i1 shift guard into foldExtractExtract.")
else:
    print("Insert point not found; no changes made.")
PY
&& submit-patch
```

